ns of racialized subaltern groups to contemporary critical race theory and cultural studies of racialization and racism. Speaking across disciplines and drawing on a number of empirical examples, Carley offers a battery of original concepts to assist scholars and activists in analyzing the tactical practices of protests in which race is a central factor.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aIdeology. 0aRace. 0aSocial movementsxPolitical aspects. 0aState, The. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aSociology : Social Change. 4aSociology : Social Movements. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847644540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438476445423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438476445/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles